## Refutation / known limits
- Guile auto-compiled .go files in ~/.cache/guile/ccache can
  carry stale version constants from before this commit. We hit
  this during smoke testing — the welcome banner showed v0.5.0
  after editing version.scm to v0.6.0 because the cache was
  newer than my cache invalidation logic understood. Workaround:
  rm -rf ~/.cache/guile/ccache && gmake clean && gmake. Worth
  surfacing in the README troubleshooting section.
- The version-string function is duplicated in spirit across
  src/sage/version.scm and a few status displays. A single
  source of truth would be cleaner.

## Meta - research / context / deep-dives
- Tag conventions: this repo uses v0.X.Y. The tag command in
  the Makefile (gmake tag) handles it.
- The release process per Makefile help:
  1. gmake patch/minor/major  (already done — minor)
  2. git add -A && git commit  (NO — we use stacked progressive
     commits, see project memory feedback_stacked_diffs_with_notes.md)
  3. gmake tag                 (creates v0.6.0 tag)
  4. git push && git push --tags
  5. gmake release             (gh release create)
- Notes are NOT pushed by default. To share these notes:
  git push origin refs/notes/commits
- Open question: should we adopt --depth or --shallow tags so
  the per-commit notes survive shallow clones? Probably not
  worth the complexity for a small repo.
- Worth a follow-up: a gmake notes-push target that does the
  refs/notes/commits push so users don't have to remember the
  ref name.
